Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees.

Slice @demi-baguette{1} crosswise into 8 rounds. Spread slices out on a #baking sheet{}
and drizzle with @oil{}. Toast on top rack of oven until golden brown, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, season @ricotta{4%oz} with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Spread ricotta onto toasted baguette slices
and top with @Mike's Hot Honey{3%tbsp}. Serve immediately.

> Spicy, creamy, sweet—all in one bite. Great for small get-togethers or grazing.